ExternalReferences.DisorderMappingRelation: NTBT (ORPHAcode is narrower than the targeted code used to represent it)

TextSection.Contents: A clonal B-cell disorder characterized by the aggregation and deposition of insoluble amyloid fibrils derived from misfolding of monoclonal immunoglobulin light chains. It usually presents as systemic AL amyloidosis with involvement of one or more parenchymal organ(s) and less frequently as localized amyloidosis with usually nodular deposits restricted to a single organ and/or system.

Parent.Label: Non-genetic systemic disease with glomerulopathy as a major feature

Phenotype.HPOTerm: Increased troponin T level in blood
